<p>Your keyword rankings look solid on paper. You track 200 terms. Forty of them sit on page one. But your organic traffic barely moved last quarter. Something does not add up.</p>
<p>The problem is not your rankings. The problem is what those rankings actually mean in terms of clicks, impressions, and real search presence. A position 8 ranking for a 50,000-volume keyword delivers less traffic than a position 2 ranking for a 5,000-volume keyword. Raw position data hides this truth.</p>
<p>This is where <strong>SEO visibility score</strong> changes the game. It is a single percentage that tells you exactly how much of the total organic click opportunity your website captures across your tracked keywords. No more spreadsheet gymnastics. No more guessing whether a ranking drop on one term matters more than a gain on another.</p>
