<p><strong>Action:</strong> For your top 50 keywords, identify which SERP features appear. Create content specifically formatted to win each feature type.</p>
<h3>5. Fix Technical SEO Issues</h3>
<p>Technical problems cap your visibility. A site with excellent content but slow load times, mobile rendering issues, or crawl errors will never reach its potential.</p>
<p><strong>Priority fixes:</strong>
- Core Web Vitals (LCP under 2.5s, INP under 200ms, CLS under 0.1)
- Mobile usability errors
- Index bloat (remove or noindex thin pages)
- Broken internal links
- Duplicate content and canonical issues
- XML sitemap accuracy</p>
<p>Run a <a href="/blog/technical-seo-checklist/">technical SEO checklist</a> audit monthly. Fix critical issues within 48 hours.</p>
<h3>6. Build Strategic Backlinks to Pages Ranking 4-10</h3>
<p>Pages in positions 4 through 10 often lack the authority to break into the top 3. A targeted backlink campaign can push them over the line.</p>
<p><strong>Action:</strong> Identify your 10 highest-value pages ranking positions 4-10. Run a <a href="/blog/backlink-audit-guide/">backlink audit</a> on the pages currently ranking 1-3 for those terms. Target the same referring domains with outreach, digital PR, or guest content.</p>
<h3>7. Improve Click-Through Rates</h3>
<p>Visibility score assumes a standard CTR curve. If your listings get higher-than-expected CTRs, you effectively increase your visibility without changing rankings.</p>
<p><strong>Tactics:</strong>
- Write title tags that include the exact keyword plus a specific benefit
- Add numbers, years, and brackets to titles (e.g., "7 Ways to Improve SEO Visibility [2026 Guide]")
- Craft meta descriptions that promise a specific outcome
- Use <a href="/blog/schema-markup-seo-guide/">schema markup</a> to add star ratings, prices, or FAQ rich snippets</p>
<p><strong>Action:</strong> A/B test title tag changes on your top 20 pages. Track CTR in Google Search Console for 30 days before and after.</p>
