<h3>Correlating Visibility with Business Outcomes</h3>
<p>Visibility score is a leading indicator. Traffic is a lagging indicator. Revenue is the ultimate metric. Connect all three.</p>
<p><strong>Method:</strong> Create a simple dashboard that plots visibility score, organic sessions, and conversions on the same timeline. Look for correlations. A visibility increase should precede a traffic increase by 2 to 4 weeks. Traffic increases should precede conversion increases by 1 to 2 weeks.</p>
<p>If visibility rises but traffic does not, check:
- Are your rankings for high-volume terms actually improving, or just low-volume terms?
- Are SERP features stealing clicks?
- Is there a mismatch between tracked keywords and actual search behavior?</p>
<p>If traffic rises but conversions do not, check:
- Are you ranking for informational terms that do not drive purchases?
- Is your landing page experience poor?
- Are you attracting the wrong audience?</p>
